geoffrey.skelley: But with just seven candidates, there‚Äôs a chance Klobuchar, Steyer and Yang could all get a bit more time to make their case tonight. And that could make a difference, particularly for Steyer and Yang, who spoke the fewest words in the last debate.
perry: Klobuchar has lucked out in that she is the only candidate on tonight‚Äôs stage with traditional credentials, outside the top four. (Harris would have fit in this group as well, but she‚Äôs dropped out.) Now I don‚Äôt think this necessarily means Klobuchar will pick up support, but she is the most logical person for people to go to next if they have concerns about the top four.
