sarahf: On that note, I‚Äôm going to go off book and give you all a wager from my ~mind~ (dangerous, I know). Let‚Äôs talk about how many candidates win 15 percent or more of the statewide vote in Iowa, which is the mechanism by which candidates win delegates (this is different than the viability threshold Geoff mentioned above, which looks at each caucus site individually ‚Äî confusing, I know). Since 1992 when the 15 percent threshold was first introduced, there‚Äôs never been a primary or caucus (in Iowa or elsewhere) where four or more candidates have earned more than 15 percent of the statewide vote, but there have been many instances where three candidates have cleared it. So, first up ‚Äî buy, sell, hold: Three candidates win 15 percent of the vote in Iowa this year (45 percent).
