nrakich: My pushback to that, Perry, is that he‚Äôs only weak in the first two early states, and there ‚Äúweak‚Äù just means ‚Äúnot in first place.‚Äù It would be entirely unsurprising to me if he gains a few points and wins both Iowa and New Hampshire in the end.
geoffrey.skelley: Based on my analysis of early primary polls earlier this year, a candidate polling at about 25 percent nationally in the second half of the year before the primary has around a 25 percent chance of winning the nomination.
