sarahf: Which‚Ä¶ considering this was the fourth primary debate, how does it fit in with the debates we‚Äôve seen already? I know we chatted about how maybe debates don‚Äôt matter all that much for the horse-race on Tuesday, and how it‚Äôs more about understanding the direction the party is moving in ‚Äî but do you think that was the case tonight? Or do you think we‚Äôll see some horse race movement?
seth.masket: Twelve people seemed like too many, but CNN largely handled that by ignoring about a third of the stage most of the time.
