There‚Äôs the early-state poll route, too, but no one‚Äôs strength is quite so disproportionately concentrated in Iowa, New Hampshire, Nevada or South Carolina that anyone‚Äôs getting two polls of 5 percent while not also getting four polls of 3 percent or more.
