If you‚Äôve ever been at a dinner party, you‚Äôll understand the following dynamic: It‚Äôs late. The conversation is deadly dull. Dessert still hasn‚Äôt been served. You‚Äôre bored and exhausted and want nothing more than to go home and go to bed. But you don‚Äôt want to be the first person to leave.Eventually, somebody decides it‚Äôs grown late enough. She makes an excuse to leave. Now there‚Äôs safety in numbers. You can leave because other people are leaving. And the dinner party ends. Suddenly.
