FiveThirtyEight is looking for an experienced reporter to join our team and cover the intersection of politics and race. It‚Äôs not hard to find an example of what they‚Äôd cover. Race is an element in so many political stories, even if the media doesn‚Äôt acknowledge as much. We‚Äôre interested in making that clear for readers, and in exploring how identity, racism and America‚Äôs history on race inform and affect contemporary politics ‚Äî whether it be a story emerging out of the White House or from the campaign trail.
The ideal candidate will be someone who‚Äôs experienced in reporting on race, identity and/or demographics, and who wants to make explicit what‚Äôs often lurking in politics. They‚Äôll mix a savvy understanding of data ‚Äì where to find it, what to do with it and how to interpret it ‚Äì with traditional reporting skills to advance FiveThirtyEight‚Äôs mission: using empiricism to help make sense of the world.
