He speaks directly to the camera about how the alleged gunman in the El Paso shooting used language similar to President Trump‚Äôs when writing about his motivations for the attack, and I think Castro comes across as a very effective messenger because he makes it so personal. He says people who ‚Äúlook like me, [who] look like my family‚Äù (i.e., Latinos) have come under attack during the Trump administration. And as Amelia wrote recently, many Latinos in the U.S. say things have gotten worse under Trump.
